rmk: This is a recording of a vocalization we collected while doing some point counts in peatswamp forest.  The sounds were not terribly far away (maybe 30 m) but we could not get a view of the birds making the sound (there were at least two individuals based on our estimates of the locations of the sound and you might hear they overlap one another in some of the sounds).  Does Chalcophaps indica make any other sound than the typical sound heard in this recording that occurs in the range of 260-560 hz?  The mystery sound is a sort of growling purring sound that ranges between 100 - 600 hz.
